node.text: She popped up on my photo memories today #flashbackfriday 📸

Highlighting a two part series we did on @candicekayla … Meredith Berkaman is the founder of @parents_against_vaping . After listening to a podcast series called “The Vaping Fix” we knew we needed to do a deep dive into the epidemic of teen vaping. I know, I know… if you’re young reading this I probably sound SO old right now. My intention is only to highlight the manipulation of these companies so that you can take your power back and understand the choices you are making vs. the ones that are being made for you. I even talk about my own struggles with nicotine. So no judgment or shaming here! Just facts that you can do with what you will 👍 Check it out #directionallychallengedpod

node.text: A few months ago I went back to work for the first time in a long time. After being quarantined for a year and a half, and having a second child who was still an infant, I somehow didn’t anticipate how many mixed emotions would come into play being away from home. Then I found myself on a set full of incredible, bad ass, strong, creative, and caring women & mothers. Their understanding, encouragement, and welcoming of my vulnerabilities will stick with me for a long time. These portraits were taken by our First AC @traiana7 on a 35mm film camera on location between shots. 📸 check her out if you like photography 👍

node.text: Used my summer break from social media  to study art of tik toking youth from yesteryears way of staying up on current events…glossy magazines. I learned that I will leave the tik toking and snap chatting to the youth and stay in my lane with simply posting excessively filtered photographs taken by my five year old. The elder is back on the gram 📸
